eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Histologically proven large B-cell lymphoma
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Histologically proven large B-cell lymphoma including the following types defined by WHO 2016: DLBCL not otherwise specified (including ABC/GCB); HGBL with or without MYC and BCL2 and/or BCL6 rearrangement; DLBCL arising from FL; T-cell/histiocyte rich large B-cell lymphoma; DLBCL associated with chronic inflammation; Primary cutaneous DLBCL, leg type; Epstein-Barr virus (EBV) + DLBCL

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Relapsed or refractory disease
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Relapsed or refractory disease after first-line chemoimmunotherapy. Refractory disease defined as no complete remission to first-line therapy; subjects who are intolerant to first-line therapy are excluded (Progressive disease (PD) as best response; Stable disease (SD) as best response after at least 4 cycles; PR as best response after at least 6 cycles and biopsy-proven residual disease or disease progression ≤ 12 months of therapy). Relapsed disease defined as complete remission to first-line therapy followed by biopsy-proven disease relapse ≤ 12 months of first-line therapy

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Adequate first-line therapy
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subjects must have received adequate first-line therapy including at a minimum: Anti-CD20 monoclonal antibody unless investigator determines that tumor is CD20 negative, and An anthracycline containing chemotherapy regimen

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Intent to proceed to HDT and ASCT
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Intent to proceed to HDT and ASCT if response to second-line therapy

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Radiographically documented disease
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subjects must have radiographically documented disease

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: No CNS involvement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: No known history or suspicion of central nervous system (CNS) involvement by lymphoma

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Prior systemic cancer therapy washout
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: At least 2 weeks or 5 half-lives, whichever is shorter, must have elapsed since any prior systemic cancer therapy at the time the subject provides consent

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Age requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Age 18 years or older at the time of informed consent

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: ECOG performance status
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: ECOG performance status of 0 or 1

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Adequate organ function
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Adequate bone marrow, renal, hepatic, pulmonary and cardiac function defined as: ANC ≥1000/µL; Platelet count ≥ 75,000/µL; Absolute lymphocyte count ≥ 100/µL; Creatinine clearance ≥ 60 mL/min; ALT/AST ≤ 2.5 ULN; Total bilirubin ≤ 1.5 mg/dl (except Gilbert’s); Cardiac ejection fraction ≥ 50%, no evidence of pericardial effusion, and no clinically significant ECG findings; No clinically significant pleural effusion; Baseline oxygen saturation > 92% on room air

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Pregnancy test requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Females of childbearing potential must have a negative serum or urine pregnancy test (females who have undergone surgical sterilization or who have been postmenopausal for at least 2 years are not considered to be of childbearing potential)

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: History of other malignancy
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of malignancy other than nonmelanoma skin cancer or carcinoma in situ (eg, cervix, bladder, breast) unless disease free for at least 3 years

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Richter’s transformation or PMBCL
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of Richter’s transformation of CLL or PMBCL

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Prior stem cell transplant
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of autologous or allogeneic stem cell transplant

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Lines of therapy for DLBCL
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Received more than one line of therapy for DLBCL

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Prior CD19 targeted therapy
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Prior CD19 targeted therapy

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Systemic immunostimulatory agents
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Treatment with systemic immunostimulatory agents (including, but not limited to, interferon and IL-2) within 6 weeks or 5 half-lives of the drug, whichever is shorter, prior to the first dose of axicabtagene ciloleucel or SOC

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Prior CAR T or ZUMA-7 randomization
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Prior chimeric antigen receptor therapy or other genetically modified T-cell therapy or prior randomization into ZUMA-7

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Aminoglycoside hypersensitivity
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of severe, immediate hypersensitivity reaction attributed to aminoglycosides

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Uncontrolled infection
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Presence of fungal, bacterial, viral, or other infection that is uncontrolled or requiring intravenous (IV) antimicrobials for management. Simple urinary tract infection (UTI) and uncomplicated bacterial pharyngitis are permitted if responding to active treatment.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: HIV, Hepatitis B or C
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Known history of infection with human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) or hepatitis B (HBsAg positive) or hepatitis C virus (anti-HCV positive). If there is a positive history of treated hepatitis B or hepatitis C, the viral load must be undetectable per quantitative polymerase chain reaction (PCR) and/or nucleic acid testing.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Active tuberculosis
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Active tuberculosis

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Indwelling line or drain
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Presence of any indwelling line or drain (eg, percutaneous nephrostomy tube, indwelling Foley catheter, biliary drain, or pleural/peritoneal/pericardial catheter). Dedicated central venous access catheters, such as a Port-a-Cath or Hickman catheter, are permitted.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: CSF malignant cells or brain metastases
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subjects with detectable cerebrospinal fluid malignant cells or known brain metastases or with a history of cerebrospinal fluid malignant cells or brain metastases

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Non-malignant CNS disorder
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History or presence of non-malignant CNS disorder, such as seizure disorder, cerebrovascular ischemia/hemorrhage, dementia, cerebellar disease, or any autoimmune disease with CNS involvement

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Cardiac lymphoma involvement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subjects with cardiac atrial or cardiac ventricular lymphoma involvement

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Clinically significant cardiac disease
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of myocardial infarction, cardiac angioplasty or stenting, unstable angina, New York Heart Association Class II or greater congestive heart failure, or other clinically significant cardiac disease within 12 months of enrollment

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Urgent therapy requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Requirement for urgent therapy due to tumor mass effects, such as bowel obstruction or blood vessel compression

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Autoimmune disease history
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of autoimmune disease requiring systemic immunosuppression and/or systemic disease modifying agents within the last 2 years

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Pulmonary fibrosis or pneumonitis
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis, organizing pneumonia (eg, bronchiolitis obliterans), drug-induced pneumonitis, idiopathic pneumonitis, or evidence of active pneumonitis per chest computed tomography (CT) scan at screening. History of radiation pneumonitis in the radiation field (fibrosis) is allowed.

Prior CAR T or ZUMA-7 randomization
CSF malignant cells or brain metastases
